at focusing=\r\n on one deity is the best thing to\n&gt;&gt; do, rather than trying to focus mind =\r\non ten deities and keep switching. A\n&gt;&gt; deity comes when mind and its thoug=\r\nhts are filled with that deity&#39;s name and\n&gt;&gt; mantra and other thoughts are =\r\ndriven away from the mind. Vimalananda perhaps\n&gt;&gt; wanted to motivate severa=\r\nl people to strive for vision/company of deities.\n&gt;&gt; He probably thought so=\r\nme people he has a rina with would come to earth with\n&gt;&gt; such a potential.\n=\r\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; * * *\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; Thyagaraja did compose songs on many deities. But, he fir=\r\nst had a darshan\n&gt;&gt; of Rama. He spent several years chanting Rama&#39;s name an=\r\nd had a darshan. Then\n&gt;&gt; he composed songs on many deities. However, he saw=\r\n all of them as different\n&gt;&gt; emanations from Rama. He saw Rama in all.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n&gt; Same with Aadi Shankara, Muththuswamy Deekshitar, Bammera Pothana and\n&gt;&gt; =\r\nothers.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; When one achieves perfection in surrender to one deity, one&#39;s=\r\n life is\n&gt;&gt; made. After that, one will see the same deity in all deities ev=\r\nen if he\n&gt;&gt; worships 100 deities. If one is switching between ten deities b=\r\nefore that,\n&gt;&gt; it may not be helpful in filling the mind with thoughts of a=\r\nny of those\n&gt;&gt; deities. Mind sees those deities as different objects and ma=\r\ny not fully\n&gt;&gt; surrender to any of them. Still, as I said, one may lead a f=\r\nruitful dhaarmik\n&gt;&gt; life. That&#39;s fine.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; But, if you really want to tas=\r\nte the nectar of complete surrender, it is\n&gt;&gt; better to pick one deity and =\r\nfill the mind with his/her thoughts.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; * * *\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt; Excellent answers =\r\non each thread and mother showed her divine\n&gt;&gt; &gt; grace through you that I a=\r\nm able to find answers to many\n&gt;&gt; &gt; questions th